 Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2000\n| Ricky Tognazzi\n| ''[[Canone inverso]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2001\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''Mal\u00e8na''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| NA\n| Career\n| 50th Anniversary David\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2007\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''[[La Sconosciuta]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''Baar\u00eca''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''The Best Offer''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2016\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''[[The Correspondence]]''\n| Best Composer\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n'''[[European Film Awards]]'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border:2px #aaa solid; font-size:90%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Director\n! Project\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n| 1999\n| NA\n| Career\n| Lifetime Achievement Award\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| [[Lajos Koltai]]\n| ''[[Fateless (film)|Fateless]]''\n| Best Composer\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''The Best Offer''\n| Best Composer\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| Giuseppe Tornatore\n| ''The Best Offer''\n| Best Composer\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n'''[[Los Angeles Film Critics Association|LAFCA]]'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border:2px #aaa solid; font-size:90%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Director\n! Project\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n| 1984\n| Sergio Leone\n| ''Once Upon a Time in America''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 1986\n| Roland Joff\u00e9\n| ''The Mission''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{draw|2nd Place}}\n|-\n| 2001\n| NA\n| Career\n| Career Achievement Award\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2015\n| Quentin Tarantino\n| ''[[The Hateful Eight (soundtrack)|The Hateful Eight]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{draw|2nd Place}}\n|}\n\n=== Selected other awards ===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* 1967: Diapason d'Or\n* 1969: Premio Spoleto Cinema\n* 1972: Cork Film International for ''[[La califfa]]''\n* 1979: Premio Vittorio de Sica\n* 1981: Premio della critica discografica for ''Il prato''\n* 1984: Premio Zurlini\n* 1985: Nastro d'argento and BAFTA for ''Once Upon a Time in America''\n* 1986: Premio Vittorio de Sica\n* 1988: Ninth Annual Ace Winner for ''[[Il Giorno prima]]''\n* 1989: Pardo d'Oro alla carriera [[Locarno Film Festival]]\n* 1990: Prix Fondation Sacem del XLIII Cannes Film Festival for ''Nuovo Cinema Paradiso''\n* 1992: Pentagramma d'oro\n* 1992: Premio Michelangelo\n* 1992: [[Grolla d'oro]], alla carriera (Saint Vincent)\n* 1993: Efebo d'Argento for ''Jonas che visse nella balena''\n* 1993: Globo d'oro Stampa estera in Italia\n* 1993: Gran Premio SACEM audiovisivi\n* 1994: ASCAP ''Golden Soundtrack Award'' (Los Angeles)\n* 1994: [[7 d'Or]], \"Best Music\" for ''[[La piovra]]'', {{Interlanguage link multi|La piovra (season 5)|it|3=La piovra 5 \u2013 Il cuore del problema|lt=season 5}}\n* 1995: Premio Rota\n* 1995: Golden Lion Honorary Award by the [[Venice Film Festival]]\n* 1996: Premio citt\u00e0 di Roma\n* 1996: Premio Cappelli\n* 1996: Premio [[Accademia di Santa Cecilia]]\n* 1997: [[Flaiano Prize|Premio Flaiano]]\n* 1998: Columbus Prize\n* 1999: Erich Wolfgang Korngold Internationaler Preis f\u00fcr Film\n* 1999: 'European Film Academy lifetime achievement award'\n* 2000: Honorary Degree by the University of Cagliari\n* 2001: Mikeldi de Honor at \"Zinebi \u2013 International Festival of Documentary and Short Films\" of Bilbao\n* 2002: Honorary Degree by the \"Seconda Universit\u00e0\" of Rome\n* 2003: Golden Eagle Award by the Russian National Academy of Motion Pictures Arts and Sciences of Russia for ''72&nbsp;Meters (film)''\n* 2003: Honorary Senator of the Filmscoring Class of the [[Hochschule f\u00fcr Musik und Theater M\u00fcnchen]]\n* 2006: Grand Officer [[OMRI]], nominated by [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]]\n* 2007: The Film & TV Music Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2008\u2013[[Pablo Neruda]] award, [[Chile]]'s highest award for the arts\n* 2008: Knight of the [[Legion of Honour]]\n* 2009: Medal of Merits for Macedonia<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mia.com.mk/default.aspx?mId=1&vId=66096033&lId=2&title=MACEDONIA+-+INTERNAL+AFFAIRS+ |title=Macedonian Information Agency |publisher=Mia.com.mk |date= |accessdate=13 September 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308121344/http://www.mia.com.mk/default.aspx?mId=1&vId=66096033&lId=2&title=MACEDONIA+-+INTERNAL+AFFAIRS+ |archive-date=8 March 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 2009: America Award of the [[Italy\u2013USA Foundation]]\n* 2010: [[Polar Music Prize]] of the Royal Swedish Academy of the Arts\n* 2013: Special Award for Career Achievement at the [[Online Film Critics Society|Online Film Critics Society Awards]]\n* 2013: Honoris Causa honorary academic degree at [[New Bulgarian University]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bulgariaoggi.com/it/201312112477/Italia-Bulgaria/Societ%C3%A0/Il-concerto-di-Ennio-Morricone-ha-fatto-esplodere-il-pubblico-bulgaro.html|title=New Bulgarian University awards maestro Morricone with the title \"Doctor Honoris Causa\"|publisher=eventzone.bg |date= 11 December 2013|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== General sources ==\n* Horace, B. ''Music from the Movies'', film music journal double issue 45/46, 2005: {{ISSN|0967-8131}}\n* Miceli, Sergio. ''Morricone, la musica, il cinema''. Milan: Mucchi/Ricordi, 1994: {{ISBN|978-88-7592-398-3}}\n* Miceli, Sergio. \"Morricone, Ennio\". ''The New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians'', 2nd edition, edited by [[Stanley Sadie]] and [[John Tyrrell (musicologist)|John Tyrrell]]. London: Macmillan Publishers.\n* Poppi, R., M. Pecorari. ''Dizionario del cinema italiano. I film vol. 3. Dal 1960 al 1969''. Gremese, 1993: {{ISBN|978-88-7605-593-5}}.\n* Poppi, R., M. Pecorari. ''Dizionario del cinema italiano. I film vol. 4. Dal 1970 al 1979* A/L''. Gremese, 1996: {{ISBN|978-88-7605-935-3}}.\n* Poppi, R., M. Pecorari. ''Dizionario del cinema italiano. I film vol. 4. Dal 1970 al